info.name: Alkemy OT208
info.description:
## **OT208-Java is a REST API in JAVA 11 with Spring Boot 2.5.1**

*Developed by:*

*   Nestor Raul Agredo
*   Eduardo Sanchez
*   Oriana Pellegrini
*   Martin Iriarte
*   Adrian Camus
    

*Mentor:* Juan Esteban Lopez

As part of Alkemy's acceleration for Java BackEnd. Implements functionalities for an NGO and its online management through a portal that allows access with security and differentiated by roles of Users and Administrators, facilitating the administration of partners, news, comments or contacts received from the Organization, and other features such as storing files in an AWS S3 bucket depending on the functionality, as well as the automatic sending of emails.

In addition to Spring Boot's own dependencies, the following dependencies were used:

|  |  |
| --- | --- |
| Sendgrid 4.7.2 | [Java Sendgrid](https://github.com/sendgrid/sendgrid-java) |
| JsonWebToken 0.9.1 | [Java JWT](https://github.com/auth0/java-jwt) |
| Amazon AWS SDK 1.12.220 | [AWS SDK Java](https://github.com/aws/aws-sdk-java) |
| Lombok 1.18.20 | [Proyect Lombok](https://github.com/projectlombok/lombok) |
| Sprindoc OpenApi UI 1.6.8 | [Springdoc OpenApi](https://github.com/springdoc/springdoc-openapi) |
| MySQL 8.0.25 | [MySQL Doc](https://dev.mysql.com/doc/) |
| ModelMapper 3.1.0 | [ModelMapper](https://github.com/modelmapper/modelmapper) |

## ***Entity Relationship Diagram***

![](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/85143329/175832651-337fb842-e15b-4476-b2b4-1cfa9957d663.png)

item.name: User

request.description:
StartFragment

Create a new User record, the conditions to create a User are: a First Name, a last name, an email address that respects the format, and a password of at least 8 characters and a maximum of 15. Its response, in addition to HTTPResponse, tells us through a JSON object the information of the persisted entity

EndFragment
To log in and get an API token you need to enter your registration email and password.
Example of a user login with Basic authorizations
In this endpoint a user id is supplied in the path and a validation is obtained if it exists.
Unlike the previous endpoint, in this one we must provide a valid token to obtain all the information of a user.

item.description: Endpoint with access to register new users, log in, validate users and get all the information of a user, all using Json Web Token.
